## Part 2: Async State Root Hashing Audit

### 2.1 Current Architecture: FULLY SYNCHRONOUS

The critical path is at [dag_executor.zig:370-376](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/core/dag_executor.zig#L370-L376):

```zig
// Phase 3: State Root Computation
const commit_start = std.time.nanoTimestamp();
const state_root = types.Hash{ .bytes = self.state.trie.rootHash() };
const commit_end = std.time.nanoTimestamp();
```

And `rootHash()` in [trie.zig:298-303](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/storage/verkle/trie.zig#L298-L303):

```zig
pub fn rootHash(self: *Self) [32]u8 {
    if (self.root) |root| {
        return root.getCommitment().toBytes();
    }
    return [_]u8{0} ** 32;
}
```

This calls `getCommitment()` which relies on `commit()` having been called, which does `updateCommitmentsRecursive()` — a **full bottom-up tree traversal** recomputing all Verkle polynomial commitments.

### 2.2 Impact at 400K TXs/Block (1M TPS x 400ms)

| Operation | Cost per TX | Cost per Block (400K TXs) |
|---|---|---|
| Verkle `put()` per state change | ~5 us | ~2 seconds (400K puts) |
| `updateCommitmentsRecursive()` | - | ~200-500 ms (full tree walk) |
| `rootHash()` | - | ~1 ms (commitment to bytes) |
| **Total state root phase** | - | **~2.5-3 seconds** |

**This exceeds the 400ms block time by 6-7x.** State root computation alone makes 1M TPS at 400ms blocks impossible with the current synchronous design.

### 2.3 What Exists But Is Disconnected

The codebase has **two partial solutions** that are not wired into the main execution path:

**A. Deferred Executor** ([deferred_executor.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/consensus/deferred_executor.zig)):
- Designed for execution 2 blocks behind consensus
- Has `enqueue()`, `nextToExecute()`, `markExecuted()`, `verifyStateRoot()`
- **NOT connected** to `DAGExecutor.executeBlock()` or `BlockProducer.produceDAG()`

**B. Pipeline Finalize Callback** ([pipeline.zig:332-336](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/consensus/pipeline.zig#L332-L336)):
- `on_finalize` callback fires after 2/3+1 quorum
- Designed to trigger ZephyrDB commit and WAL checkpoint
- **Does not trigger async state root computation**

**C. Checkpoint Double-Buffering** ([checkpoint.zig:60-77](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/storage/zephyrdb/checkpoint.zig#L60-L77)):
- Has double-buffered arenas (buffer_a / buffer_b)
- Background thread writes to disk while executor continues
- **Only covers checkpoint I/O, NOT Verkle root computation**

### 2.4 Status: NOT COMPLETE

Async state root hashing is **0% implemented**. The building blocks exist (deferred executor, pipeline callbacks, checkpoint threading) but the Verkle trie root computation remains fully synchronous and inline with block production.

