## Part 6: Priority Roadmap

| Priority | Optimization | Impact | Effort | Blocks 1M TPS? |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **P0** | Async state root hashing | Removes 2.5s from critical path | 3-5 days | YES |
| **P0** | Turbine SIMD + streaming | Makes block propagation viable | 3-5 days | YES |
| **P0** | Consensus timeout tuning (200ms) | Fits voting into 400ms window | 1 day | YES |
| **P1** | Memory prefetching | -200-500ns per TX | 2-3 days | Helps linearly |
| **P1** | Lock-free delta merge | -10-30ms per block | 2-3 days | Helps at scale |
| **P2** | Incremental Verkle commitments | -100ms async root time | 1-2 weeks | Not blocking |
| **P2** | Shred authentication | Security hardening | 2-3 days | Not blocking |
| **P2** | Turbine + Pipeline tests | Production reliability | 3-5 days | Not blocking |

> [!CAUTION]
> Without **Optimization 1 (Async State Root)**, 1M TPS at 400ms blocks is mathematically impossible. The synchronous Verkle root alone takes 6-7x the entire block time budget. This is the single highest priority item.
